      <p class="- topic/p ">Typical example</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Lift the carriage and the mast high enough for getting tension
on lift chains. Check the chains, and make sure the tension is the
same. Lift chains are required to check for equal tension about
every 1,000 service hours or 6 months.</p>
      <note type="warning" class="- topic/note ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Personal injury can be caused by sudden movement of the mast and carriage. Keep hands and
        feet clear of any parts that can move.</p>
